</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,476,716]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Occurs in the Pacific Ocean from 
<collectingCountry box="[548,635,511,536]" name="Mexico" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<collectingRegion box="[548,635,511,536]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Mexico</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[651,987,511,536]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref22998" refString="Hendrickx, M. E. &amp; Wicksten, M. K. (1989) Los Pandalidae del Pacifico Mexicano, con una clave para su identificacion. Caldasia, 16 (76), 71 - 86." type="journal article">Hendrickx &amp; Wicksten 1989</bibRefCitation>
) southwards to central 
<collectingCountry box="[1259,1321,511,536]" name="Chile" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref22399" refString="Guzman, G. &amp; Quiroga, E. (2005) New records of shrimps (Decapoda: Caridea and Dendrobranchiata) in deep waters off Chile. Gayana, 69 (2), 285 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.4067 / S 0717 - 65382005000200009" type="journal article">Guzmán &amp; Quiroga 2005</bibRefCitation>
) and in the southwestern Atlantic between 
<geoCoordinate box="[841,931,548,572]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" precision="925" value="-37.0">37°00'S</geoCoordinate>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[988,1179,548,573]" country="Argentina" name="Tierra del Fuego - Antartida e Islas del Atlantico Sur" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Tierra del Fuego</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1194,1344,548,573]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref28581" refString="Torti, M. R. &amp; Boschi, E. E. (1973) Nuevos aportes al conocimiento de los crustaceos decapodos Caridea del genero Campylonotus Bate, 1888. Physis, Seccion A, 32 (84), 65 - 84." type="journal article">Boschi 1973</bibRefCitation>
; Boschi 
<emphasis box="[151,208,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">et al.</emphasis>
1981, 1992; 
<bibRefCitation box="[357,502,583,608]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref27179" refString="Spivak, E. D. (1997) Los crustaceos decapodos del Atlantico sudoccidental (25 ° - 55 ° S): distribucion y ciclos de vida. Investigaciones Marinas, Valparaiso, 25, 69 - 91." type="journal article">Spivak 1997</bibRefCitation>
) and south of the 
<collectingCountry box="[706,894,583,608]" name="Falkland Islands" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Falkland Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[908,1203,583,608]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refId="ref27525" refString="Takeda, M. &amp; Hatanaka, H. (1984) Records of decapod crustaceans from the Southwestern Atlantic collected by the Japanese fisheries research trawlers. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Series A (Zoology), 10 (1), 7 - 24." type="journal article">Takeda &amp; Hatanaka 1984</bibRefCitation>
); benthic, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.066" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.13199999999999998" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="m" value="1066.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="132.0">132–2000 m</quantity>
. Boschi 
<emphasis box="[276,334,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">et al.</emphasis>
(1992) indicates 
<geoCoordinate box="[536,626,620,645]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" precision="925" value="-67.0">67°00'S</geoCoordinate>
as the southern limit for the species and Boschi &amp; Gavio (2005: table 1) state the species to be present south of the Antarctic Polar Front; both records are herein considered to be in error.
</paragraph>
